{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/map_lidar/","webpackCompilationHash":"4fe95caf3ff34ecf13cf","result":{"data":{"logo":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":400,"height":128,"src":"/static/2b5eaa0de166a8b5faebad4955c2200c/647de/ghost-logo.png","srcSet":"/static/2b5eaa0de166a8b5faebad4955c2200c/647de/ghost-logo.png 1x"}}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>A 3D-scan assembler to generate point clouds from a 2D-LIDAR.</h2>\n<p>I recently had the opportunity to work on an interesting challenge for a client. Given a 2D-LIDAR, How can we generate a 3D Point cloud of the environment? Although the problem looked daunting initially, I was able to break down the problem into fundamental components and deliver a functioning solution within 4 weeks. In this short post, we will have an high level overview of the system.</p>\n<p>Here is one snapshot of the 3D depth map generated by the system\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1170px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/5d451/3DMap.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 110.1113172541744%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"3D Map\"\n        title=\"3D Map\"\n        src=\"/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/4acc0/3DMap.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/e33f8/3DMap.jpg 293w,\n/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/d5ce0/3DMap.jpg 585w,\n/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/4acc0/3DMap.jpg 1170w,\n/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/04b0f/3DMap.jpg 1755w,\n/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/a5746/3DMap.jpg 2340w,\n/static/f5e35d5e540e994dcb4ea81de2e3cd1f/5d451/3DMap.jpg 3234w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1170px) 100vw, 1170px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The system consists of two important components:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Mechanical system that rotates the 2D-LIDAR around the third dimension. Every degree of rotation helps us acquire new 2D-depth information.</li>\n<li>Software system (ROS Node) that keeps track of the past 2D frames and stiches them together into a cohesive 3D map.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The design challenges mainly revolved around repeatability and power consumption. </p>\n<p>Have a look at the system in action.\n<img src=\"/working-a2bdfe0d247913e01011b1ad892abc44.gif\" alt=\"Working\"></p>\n<p>If you have similar requirements or another challenging project, feel free to reach out to me.</p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A 3D-scan assembler to generate point clouds from a 2D-LIDAR."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I recently had the opportunity to work on an interesting challenge for a client. Given a 2D-LIDAR, How can we generate a 3D Point cloud of the environment? Although the problem looked daunting initially, I was able to break down the problem into fundamental components and deliver a functioning solution within 4 weeks. In this short post, we will have an high level overview of the system."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here is one snapshot of the 3D depth map generated by the system\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1170px;"},"children":[{"ty